==English==
===Pronunciation===
*[[IPA]]: /æl.ˈvi.ːlɝ/ ''or'' /æl.ˈvi.ə.lɝ/
*Schoolbook Phonetics: (ălvēʹlûr) ''or'' (ălvēʹu̇lûr)
*Last Resort Phonetics: al-VEE-lurr ''or'' al-VEE-uh-lurr
===Adjective===
'''alveolar'''
#Of, or relating to an [[alveolus]]
#(''anatomy'') Relating to the [[jaw]] [[ridge]] containing the [[tooth]] [[socket]]s
#(''anatomy'') Relating to the alveoli (small [[air]] [[sac]]s) of the [[lung]]s
#(''linguistics'') Formed with the [[tip]] of the [[tongue]] touching the inner ridge of the [[gum]]s of the upper front teeth

===Noun===
'''alveolar'''
#(''linguistics'') An alveolar [[consonant]]
